RACE.RACE_TEXT: DELTA DOWNS RACE 1 6 1/2F Dirt CR: 72. Maiden Special Weight Purse 34000. FOR MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD. Weight, 120 lbs. (Preference To Horses That Have Not Started For Less Than $20,000 In Their Last Three Starts).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: HALF BROTHER tracked the leaders around the first turn then took the lead at the five sixteenths and drew clear. BRITE OUTLOOK settled in the middle of the pack around the first turn then moved up going three wide at the three eighths pole, vied for the lead around the final turn but was no match for the winner. UXMAL was four to five wide into the first turn then settled near the back into the backstretch, moved up from three to four wide through the final turn but couldn't gain on the leaders. AWESOME CAJUN was allowed to settle around the first turn then made a bid at the quarter pole and improved position in the stretch. MO MOVES raced in the middle of the pack while saving ground and passed tiring rivals in the drive. TRIPLE RED ACES was placed off the pace around the first turn then slowly faded. COOL SPIRIT set the early pace to the three eighths pole and retreated.

ENTRY.NAME: Mo Moves
ENTRY.COMMENT: middle of pack, saved ground, passed tiring rivals,

ENTRY.NAME: Brite Outlook
ENTRY.COMMENT: middle of pack, 3w3/8p, vied 2nd turn, no match

ENTRY.NAME: Awesome Cajun
ENTRY.COMMENT: allowed to settle, bid1/4p, improved position

RACE.RACE_TEXT: DELTA DOWNS RACE 2 6 1/2F Dirt CR: 72. Claiming Purse 17000. FOR FOUR YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Weight, 123 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since December 20 Allowed 3 lbs. Claiming Price $10,000 (Claiming Races For $7,500 Or Less Not Considered In Estimating Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: SERBIAN SAILOR went to a clear lead and set all the pace, was kept to task in the stretch. DARE TO FAIL was unhurried around the first turn then moved out to four wide at the three eighths pole to make a late rally and was gaining on the leader lat in the stretch but was too late. CABOCHON TREASURE was placed off the pace through the final turn but didn't make a bid. MR. WIMBLEDON BAY raced in the middle of the pack around the first turn the made a rail bid on the backstretch to the three sixteenths pole and angled out to two to three wide and finished evenly. UNCLE BRAD was forwardly placed around the first turn, made a mild rebid on the final turn and flattened out. TWIRLING CHIEF was five wide into the first turn then was allowed to settle down the backstretch while racing three to four wide but failed to menace. SONG SPECTACULAR tracked the leaders from three wide to the five sixteenths pole and gave way.

ENTRY.NAME: Serbian Sailor
ENTRY.COMMENT: clear lead, set pace, kept to task

ENTRY.NAME: Uncle Brad
ENTRY.COMMENT: forwardly placed, mild rebid, flattened out

ENTRY.NAME: Mr. Wimbledon Bay
ENTRY.COMMENT: middle of pack, rail bid, finished evenly

ENTRY.NAME: Twirling Chief
ENTRY.COMMENT: 5w1st, allowed to settle, failed to menace,

RACE.RACE_TEXT: DELTA DOWNS RACE 3 5F Dirt CR: 45. Maiden Claiming Purse 12000. FOR ACCREDITED LA BRED MAIDENS, FILLIES AND MARES FOUR YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Weight, 123 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: ROADSIDE GIRL veered in at the start then dueled for the lead to deep stretch and cleared late. A. P. STYLE broke out and bumped UMATILLA at the start then was hustled along to duel for the lead to deep stretch and weakened. DON'T BLINK TWICE dueled in the second flight from the two path to the quarter pole then made a rail bid to be up for the show. VALID BREAK broke in and bumped UMATILLA at the start then dueled in the second flight from the inside to the five sixteenths pole and was out kicked in late stretch. ELLIE'S TOUCH vied for the early lead then dueled in the second flight from the three path to the five sixteenths and proved best of the rest. CHATAIN'S EAGLE raced in the middle of the pack from four wide and improved position. UMATILLA was bumped by A.P. STYLE and VALID BREAK and was pinched back after the break and passed tiring rivals. OLD TIME GIRL hopped and the start and was not involved. CALL ME DARLIN dueled in the second flight from the four pack to the five sixteenth and gave way. ROSE OF CIMARRON pressed the pace early then dropped back and jogged in, vanned off.

ENTRY.NAME: A. P. Style
ENTRY.COMMENT: broke out, bumped, hustled along, dueled, weakened,

ENTRY.NAME: Valid Break
ENTRY.COMMENT: broke in, duel 2nd flight, out kicked

ENTRY.NAME: Don't Blink Twice
ENTRY.COMMENT: duel 2nd flight, rail bid, up show

ENTRY.NAME: Ellie's Touch
ENTRY.COMMENT: vied for lead early, duel 2nd flight, best of rest

ENTRY.NAME: Rose of Cimarron
ENTRY.COMMENT: pressed pace, dropped back, jogged in, vanned off

RACE.RACE_TEXT: DELTA DOWNS RACE 4 6 1/2F Dirt CR: 51. Maiden Claiming Purse 15000. FOR MAIDENS, FOUR YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Weight, 123 lbs. Claiming Price $10,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: SABER STORM was allowed to settle down the backstretch moved out to four wide at the three eighths pole to make a run at the leaders drifted in at the end of the final turn but was up in the final strides. PETEY went to the front to set a pressured pace was able to clear late but was nailed in the final jumps. K V TARGET was unhurried around the first turn then moved out to three wide at the three eighths pole to make a bid on the leaders, had to steady slightly and the end of the bend then made a rebid for a late run to be up for the show. CHAN veered out at the start then settled in the middle of the pack on the inside and showed late interest in the stretch drive. MIDNIGHT HUNTER was rushed to contention to the first turn then went three wide at the quarter pole to engage the leader at the three sixteenths pole and tired. FLAT OUT FABIO pressed the pace from the two path through the final turn and gave way. TRIPLE settled in the middle of the pack around the first turn then made a mild bid on the backstretch and faltered. MIDGE'S TIME was not a threat. JOCKEY OBJECTION, JOCKEY OF K V TARGET CLAIMED FOUL AGAINST THE JOCKEY OF SABER STORM FOR ALLEGED INTERFERENCE AROUND THE THREE SIXTEENTHS POLE, AFTER A STEWARDS REVIEW THE CLAIM OF FOUL WAS DISALLOWED AND NO ACTION WAS TAKEN.

ENTRY.NAME: Saber Storm
ENTRY.COMMENT: allowed to settle, 4w3/8, drift in, up final strides

ENTRY.NAME: Chan
ENTRY.COMMENT: veered out, middle of pack, late interest

ENTRY.NAME: K V Target
ENTRY.COMMENT: unhurried, 3w3/8, steadied, late run, up show

ENTRY.NAME: Triple
ENTRY.COMMENT: middle of pack, mild bid, faltered

RACE.RACE_TEXT: DELTA DOWNS RACE 5 5F Dirt CR: 65. Maiden Claiming Purse 17000. FOR MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD. Weight, 120 lbs. Claiming Price $15,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: MORO OUTLAW was bumped by MADELYN'S SOLDIER at the start, raced in the middle of the pack down the backstretch made a rail bid on the turn then moved out to the two path in upper stretch and drew clear. PROPERLY CONNECTED bumped MORO OUTLAW at the start then was hustled to the lead and pulled away at the quarter pole but was caught in the final sixteenth and held the place. A SOLDIER'S WAY raced in the middle of the pack then made a three wide bid at the quarter pole for a late run to be up for the show. IN DETAIL was off the pace and chased the leaders around the turn but was out finished. MADELYN'S SOLDIER broke in and bumped MORO OUTLAW at the start then raced near the back down the backstretch, was four wide at the five sixteenths pole and show late interest. WINNY'SSPECIALSTAR lacked early speed then made a rail bid on the turn to improve position. RED RAIDER XPRESS bobbled at the start and bumped PROPERLY CONNECTED, raced five wide on the backstretch but was not a threat. ALL COUNTRY raced in the middle of the pack but was not a threat. GOLDEN REMEDY shot away from the gate and pressed the pace from the two path but gave way.

ENTRY.NAME: Properly Connected
ENTRY.COMMENT: bumped, hustled to lead, pulled away, caught, held place

ENTRY.NAME: Madelyn's Soldier
ENTRY.COMMENT: broke in, bumped, back, 4w5/16p, late interest

ENTRY.NAME: A Soldier's Way
ENTRY.COMMENT: middle of pack, 3wbid, late run, up show

ENTRY.NAME: Moro Outlaw
ENTRY.COMMENT: bumped, middle of pack, rail bid, drew clear,

ENTRY.NAME: Golden Remedy
ENTRY.COMMENT: broke well, pressed pace, gave way,

ENTRY.NAME: In Detail
ENTRY.COMMENT: off pace, chased leaders, out finished

RACE.RACE_TEXT: DELTA DOWNS RACE 6 7F Dirt CR: 81. Allowance Purse 43000. FOR ACCREDITED LA BRED FOUR YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Weight, 123 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since December 20 Allowed 3 lbs. A Race Since November 20 Allowed 6 lbs. (Claiming Races Not Considered In Estimating Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: HOLIDAY DIAMOND tracked the leaders to the final turn then moved to engage the leader at the three sixteenths pole and dueled down the stretch and just lasted. KING OF CONTRABAND settled in the middle of the pack from off the rail down the backstretch, made a bid at the quarter pole on the leaders, closed well but was too late. GOTMY MO JO WORKIN was rushed to a clear lead to the final turn the was headed at the three sixteenths pole and dueled down the stretch but was out finished. HEZA PICKLE was unhurried around the first turn then moved up from five to six wide on the backstretch and finished evenly. SOULOLOGY settled in the middle of the pack on the inside lacked room into the final turn and failed to menace. JAMAICAN ME was never a threat. WILLIE THE MAN was rank around the first turn the placed off the pace to the quarter pole and gave way.

ENTRY.NAME: Holiday Diamond
ENTRY.OWNER: Sebastien Ronald J and Sebastien Linda P
ENTRY.COMMENT: tracked leader, engaged 3/16p, dueled, just lasted,

ENTRY.NAME: Soulology
ENTRY.COMMENT: middle of pack, inside, lacked room, failed to menace,

ENTRY.NAME: King of Contraband
ENTRY.COMMENT: middle of pack, off rail, bid 1/4p, closed well, too late

ENTRY.NAME: Gotmy Mo Jo Workin
ENTRY.COMMENT: rushed to lead, headed 3/16p, dueled, out finished

RACE.RACE_TEXT: DELTA DOWNS RACE 7 5F Dirt CR: 61. Maiden Special Weight Purse 34000. FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES THREE YEARS OLD. Weight, 120 lbs. (Preference To Horses That Have Not Started For Less Than $20,000 In Their Last Three Starts).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: THROWBACK pressed the pace from the two path then took the lead at the quarter pole, pulled away and prevailed. FREEBRITNEY was forwardly placed down the backstretch then made a three wide bid but was no match for the winner. MISS LONELYHEARTS hopped at the start, made a three wide bid on the turn then moved out to four wide in upper stretch and rallied for the show. CALIFORNIA BELLE raced in the middle of the pack then made a four wide bid at the five sixteenths pole and flattened out. HELLO MARYLOU raced in the middle of the pack from the tow path then made a mild bid into the stretch but was empty. ALABAMA QUEEN was void of the early speed and lacked racing room going into the turn, had to check slightly and passed tiring rivals. HIDDEN LOVE was placed off the pace on the inside to the three eighths pole the drifted in and out going into the turn and gave way. FOLLOW THROUGH had the early speed then was headed at the quarter pole and tired.

ENTRY.NAME: Hidden Love
ENTRY.COMMENT: off pace, drifted in, gave way,

ENTRY.NAME: Alabama Queen
ENTRY.COMMENT: no speed, lacked room, passed tiring rivals,

ENTRY.NAME: Hello Marylou
ENTRY.COMMENT: middle of pack, mild bid, empty

RACE.RACE_TEXT: DELTA DOWNS RACE 8 5F Dirt CR: 84. Allowance Purse 44000. FOR ACCREDITED LA BRED FOUR YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES OTHER THAN MAIDEN, CLAIMING, STARTER OR TRIAL OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES. Weight, 123 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since December 20 Allowed 3 lbs. A Race Since Novembe r 20 Allowed 6 lbs. (Claiming Races For $15,000 Or Less Not Considered In Estimating Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: AZTAR was close up on the leaders from the five path, took the lead at the eighth pole, inched away and held on. MUCHO MARVIN chased the leaders around the turn and gained late on the winner. GUITAR DOCTOR sprinted to the lead from under pressure then was headed at the eighth pole and gave way grudgingly. IRON IN THE FIRE tracked the leaders from the six path to the turn then made a four wide bid at the quarter pole and flattened out. G DON'T KNOW vied for the lead from the two path and was in tight going into the turn then dropped back and finished evenly. TRIPPER JOHN vied for the lead from the inside to the five sixteenths and stopped.

ENTRY.NAME: G Don't Know
ENTRY.COMMENT: vied for lead, in tight, dropped back, evenly

ENTRY.NAME: Guitar Doctor
ENTRY.COMMENT: sprint to lead, headed 1/8p, gave way grudgingly

RACE.RACE_TEXT: DELTA DOWNS RACE 9 6 1/2F Dirt CR: 55. Claiming Purse 12000. FOR FILLIES AND MARES FOUR YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Weight, 123 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since December 20 Allowed 3 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: IN FOR A PENNY had early speed, led or vied for the lead from the inside through the final turn then made a rebid at the top of the stretch to duel down the stretch and won the nod. RYAN'S GRACE vied for the lead or lead from the two path through the final turn then dueled down the stretch and was out nodded. MILA'S KAT was five wide into the first turn then stalked the pace, moved up on the backstretch and made a late run in the stretch to be up for the show. SUMMER IS HOT was placed off the pace around the first turn then pressed the pace down the backstretch to the top of the lane and weakened. COUSIN VICKIE saved ground through the final turn then moved out to four wide in the stretch run to pass tiring rivals. THURSDAY MORNING was not a factor. INPENDING BREEZE tracked the leaders from the two path and failed to menace. FANCY BLAZE settled in the middle of the pack on the inside, made a mild bid on the final turn but was empty in the drive. MO DIXIE DIVA raced near the back around the first turn then made a five wide bid on the backstretch but was not a threat. CABO SUNSET remained back and was vanned off.

ENTRY.NAME: In for a Penny
ENTRY.COMMENT: led, vied for lead, rebid, dueled, won nod

ENTRY.NAME: Ryan's Grace
ENTRY.COMMENT: vied for lead, led, dueled, out nodded

ENTRY.NAME: Fancy Blaze
ENTRY.COMMENT: middle of pack, mild bid, empty

ENTRY.NAME: Mila's Kat
ENTRY.COMMENT: 5w1st, stalked pace, moved up, late run, up show
